fr.ecp.Group52_Project_IS1220_part1_AVEROUS_TOPUZ.Model.Network

Class Network

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.ecp.Group52_Project_IS1220_part1_AVEROUS_TOPUZ.Model.Network.Network
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    VisitableItems

    public class Network
extends java.lang.Object
implements VisitableItems
    The myVelib global network. It contains all users, all stations, and all bikes present in the myVelib System. THe network is used to create new instances of Stations, Users, or Bikes.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Pierre Averous, Nicolas Topuz

      • Network

        public Network(java.lang.String name,
               int numberOfStations,
               int slotsPerStation,
               double fillingPercentage)
        throws InvalidProportionsException
        The constructor for making a Network instance. This constructor creates a Network in which the Stations are located at random in a square of side 4 on the earth's surface. This is the default constructor for making a Network within a square.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the network, as a String
        numberOfStations - The number of stations to be built in the network, as an int
        slotsPerStation - The number of parking slots to build within each station, as an int
        fillingPercentage - The filling rate of each station with bikes, as a double
        Throws:
        InvalidProportionsException

      • Network

        public Network(java.lang.String name,
               int numberOfStations,
               int slotsPerStation,
               double sideArea,
               double fillingPercentage)
        throws InvalidProportionsException
        The constructor for making a Network instance. This constructor creates a Network in which the Stations are located at random in a square of side sideArea on the earth's surface.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the network, as a String
        numberOfStations - The number of stations to be built in the network, as an int
        slotsPerStation - The number of parking slots to build within each station, as an int
        sideArea - The side of the square will randomly pop into (in km) as a double
        fillingPercentage - The filling rate of each station with bikes, as a double
        Throws:
        InvalidProportionsException
